Use the correct SUPIR model, SUPIR-v0F or SUPIR-v0Q. I didn't saw much difference at the end of the workflow using 1 or the other.

Where there is a big difference is the checkpoint that it merge with. I use wowXL420_v420 but had good experience with realvisxlV40_LighthingBakeVAE with lower steps of course.

The Upscale stack can be use to control some unwanted artifact in picture. I usually put all to off. If you use, keep using rescale to 1 and don't use 2x or above as they will slow the process very much.

If there is deformation, hair at place that shouldn't be or some error, try to play with: 

SUPIR sampler settings:
-Steps, 15-50
-cfg_scale_start, 1-6
-cfg_scale_end, 2-6

SUPIR encoder settings:
-encoder_tile_size, 512 or 768

Positive and negative prompt:
-Anything to help remove or add wanted or unwanted thing.

If you get any out of memory, try putting, use_tiled_vae to true in node SUPIR First Stage (Denoiser) 

The lora (DetailedEyes_V3)can be changed but I found this one in particular very good to add fine detail, and not only in eyes

Be sure to have all the checkpoints and models before you start.

EVERYTHING ELSE can stay the same for portrait pictures bigger of 512x512.
You can try to play with setting but those work very well already.

The title of each group node say pretty much what you have to know. Put it on if needed.

-Model used:
wowXL420_V420
realvisxlV30Turbo_v30Bakedvae
SUPIR-v0F
stablesr_768v-000139
webui_768v_139
-Upscaler:
4x_NMKD-Superscale-SP_178000_G (add texture to skin, use 4x-ultrasharp for anime or other clean picture)
-Controlnet model:
sai_xl_depth_256lora (to control deformation of ultimateSD upscale. Not needed if denoise stay under 0.25 in ultimate.

Be carful with CCSR as it take a lot of video resources and it do restart everytime you queue prompt even if there is no change and fixed seed.
Multiple custom node required. Manager should tell wich one you need, go to their web page to see if there is any requirements to pip install -r requirements.txt

Also, the node FRED_AutoCropImage_SDXL_Ratio is 1 of my custom node, copy the .py inside your \ComfyUI\custom_nodes.

Put Auto_find_SDXL_resolution to True if you want
the system to find the closest SDXL ratio that fit in your picture. 
If you put it to off, choose a ratio or utilise Custom to put your custom crop value. 

The node will NOT resize your picture, it will only crop it and return the scale_factor
needed to reach that size. 
If you put a prescale_factor, it will multiply by the scale_factor

If you want to crop from the center, set crop_from_center to True
otherwise, you can adjust crop_x and crop_y to change the cropping area
starting from the top left corner

Face detection is done using Haar Cascade Cascade Classifier.
Choose the cascade_xml file you want to use.
Adjust offset to upscale the detection area.
